{
    "title": "Epsilon transition",
    "html": "<div class=\"flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[3px]\"><div class=\"markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert dark\"><p>Yes, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ε</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varepsilon</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ε</span></span></span></span>-transitions are allowed <strong>only in NFA</strong>, not in DFA. Here's a detailed explanation of how <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ε</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varepsilon</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ε</span></span></span></span>-transitions work and their implications:</p><hr><h3><strong>What is an <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ε</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varepsilon</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ε</span></span></span></span>-Transition?</strong></h3><p>An <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ε</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varepsilon</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ε</span></span></span></span>-transition is a transition in an NFA that allows the automaton to move from one state to another without consuming any input symbol.</p><h4>Example:</h4><p>If there is an <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ε</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varepsilon</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ε</span></span></span></span>-transition from state <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">q_1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.625em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.03588em;\">q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0359em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">&ZeroWidthSpace;</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> to state <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">q_2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.625em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.03588em;\">q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0359em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">&ZeroWidthSpace;</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, the automaton can \"jump\" to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">q_2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.625em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.03588em;\">q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0359em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">&ZeroWidthSpace;</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> without reading any symbol from the input.</p><hr><h3><strong>Why Use <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ε</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varepsilon</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ε</span></span></span></span>-Transitions?</strong></h3><ol><li><strong>Simplifies construction:</strong><ul><li>They allow combining smaller NFAs (e.g., in union or concatenation of regular languages).</li></ul></li><li><strong>Efficient representation:</strong><ul><li><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ε</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varepsilon</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ε</span></span></span></span>-transitions make it easier to represent certain patterns in regular languages.</li></ul></li></ol><hr><h3><strong>Behavior of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ε</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varepsilon</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ε</span></span></span></span>-Transitions:</strong></h3><p>When an NFA processes an input string, it considers all possible paths, including those that use <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ε</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varepsilon</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ε</span></span></span></span>-transitions. Before reading a symbol from the input, the automaton can:</p><ul><li>Take any <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ε</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varepsilon</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ε</span></span></span></span>-transition and move to one or more states.</li><li>Combine this behavior with regular transitions.</li></ul><h4>Example Trace:</h4><ol><li>Starting in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">q_0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.625em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.03588em;\">q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0359em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">&ZeroWidthSpace;</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, if there is an <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ε</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varepsilon</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ε</span></span></span></span>-transition to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">q_1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.625em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.03588em;\">q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0359em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">&ZeroWidthSpace;</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, the automaton can \"visit</li></ol></div></div>"
